🎯 What is SCM (Software Configuration Management)
📌 Simple definition:

SCM is the process of managing and tracking changes in software code.

🧠 In easy words:

SCM helps you:

Track what changed
Know who changed it
Go back to old version if needed
Work in team without conflict
🧱 Why SCM is needed

Without SCM:
❌ Code gets overwritten
❌ No history
❌ Team conflicts

With SCM:
✅ Safe changes
✅ Version history
✅ Team collaboration

